      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "86d992bc_e862f71f",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/charts/aai-graphadmin/templates/job.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 197,
      "message": "Yes, actually had to use it because for upgrade from Casablanca to Dublin we have different clusters.\nThinking about more generic way of finding out which cluster is available for backup.\nThis is responsible for backup only so will connect to aai-cassandra (if present) otherwise to shared cassandra to take backup.\nThe migration job which is post-upgrade hook would always connect to the shared cassandra to restore/migrate.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2763,
        "name": "Mahendra Raghuwanshi",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mahendra.raghuwanshi@amdocs.com",
        "username": "mahendrr"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-08 10:40:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "2226c631_15197675",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "5c6c782d_2d2f257e",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/charts/aai-resources/resources/config/janusgraph-cached.properties",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 34,
      "message": "No its not dependent on this gerrit.\nI am using the shared cassandra service name as hostname as now shared cassandra would be in different release (eg. dev-cassandra) which has to be provided here using ugly override if we want to provide the hostnames of all the replicas of cluster if needed.\nThe service is load-balancing between the endpoints.\nWith correct replication factor, should we care about it?\n\nBTW, shared cassandra has been merged and we can now enable that using --set cassandra.enabled=true",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2763,
        "name": "Mahendra Raghuwanshi",
        "display_name": null,
