    {
      "id": "9db52661_51d20294",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/helm/plugins/deploy/deploy.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 221,
      "message": "If we are using hooks, then helm does not come out of the helm upgrade until all the hooks have completed. \nWhen you want to install aai and shared cassandra and aai has hooks running then it will not come out as we will not have shared cassandra installed (installation happens based on names). So need to run helm upgrades in parallel.\n\nWill be applicable to any other components as well which have cross component dependencies.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 2763,
        "name": "Mahendra Raghuwanshi",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "mahendra.raghuwanshi@amdocs.com",
        "username": "mahendrr"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-08 10:40:29.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5ca4ecf4_40b67952",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "2ff747bc_431e98e8",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/charts/aai-graphadmin/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 49,
      "message": "Please do not mix together the concepts of \"container ready\" and \"job complete\". That is confusing.\nIt should be the choice of the ONAP project to set the conditions they need for their microservices.\nAnd the naming should be clear!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4341,
        "name": "Keong Lim",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
        "username": "keong"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-12 03:37:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "a9e6f0ba_59e434ff",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "71484b25_6fcd8f07",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/charts/aai-graphadmin/templates/deployment.yaml",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 52,
      "message": "Please do not mix together the concepts of \"normal startup\" and \"upgrade migration\". That is confusing.\nIt should be the choice of the ONAP project to set the procedures they need for their microservices.\nAnd the naming should be clear!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4341,
        "name": "Keong Lim",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
        "username": "keong"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-12 03:37:39.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "782fedc7_5400b482",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "efb1da45_344fc8de",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/aai/charts/aai-resources/resources/config/janusgraph-cached.properties",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 34,
      "message": "from https://docs.datastax.com/en/cassandra/3.0/cassandra/architecture/archDataDistributeReplication.html\n\n\"As a general rule, the replication factor should not exceed the number of nodes in the cluster.\"\n\nSo for a replica count of 1 and replication factor of 3, it is will limit the capacity of the database to one-third of disk space, unless other changes are made.\n\nThat is a big caveat to document!",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4341,
        "name": "Keong Lim",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
        "username": "keong"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-12 03:45:21.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "5c6c782d_2d2f257e",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "0c1aa9da_a63e554c",
      "file_path": "kubernetes/helm/plugins/deploy/deploy.sh",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 221,
      "message": "If the upgrades are not completed and other ONAP projects are dependent on it, then they also cannot be completed.\nSo why run them in parallel if they would be blocked from completion still?",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 4341,
        "name": "Keong Lim",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "keong.lim+onap@gmail.com",
        "username": "keong"
      },
      "updated": "2019-03-12 03:57:20.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "9db52661_51d20294",
      "unresolved": false
    }
